OL,3,CUK defence 'spending gap' is 'matter
OL,4,Cof concern for Nato', says former chief
OL,6,FLast year's Nato summit in The Hague
OL,7,Fsaw allies including the UK agree to
OL,8,Fspend 5% of GDP on defence under
OL,9,Fpressure from Donald Trump, who had
OL,10,Fcast doubt on US support for the
OL,11,Falliance and accused European nations
OL,12,Fof freeloading on American defence.
OL,14,FSpain was the only country to secure
OL,15,Fan opt-out, capping spending at 2.1%
OL,16,Finstead ` up from its current level of
OL,17,Faround 1.2%.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
